The paper deals with the optimization of pricing strategies in a mobile market with multiple actors, including Mobile Network Operators (MNOs) and a Mobile Virtual Network Operator (MVNO). This involves game-theoretical analysis and optimization techniques, which are commonly used in the field of Game Theory (cs.GT) and Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the use of different technologies and revenue sources, which are relevant to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of pricing strategies, which is relevant to Computational Economics (cs.CE).
